{"author":{"id":"8e1777f58c0cfe5478428be8f9fcbfe90d25e44689578335da8fc2246fe0915a"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1736332316,"nonce":"IqXXEpU4JCSH6Ho4wfJKzoXH0Wc=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s6ZnwK3","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6661#issuecomment-2577334967"},"message":"Hi @BioinformaticsPlatformWIV-ISP!\n\n[TMPDIR](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TMPDIR) is a standard UNIX variable that indicates a temporary folder. We use it a lot in our tools https://github.com/search?q=repo%3Agalaxyproject%2Ftools-iuc+TMPDIR+language%3AXML\u0026type=code\u0026l=XML\n\nGalaxy tools are intended to describe the underlying tool in a way, that we do expose as less as possible Galaxy intrinsic, so I would like to avoid using `GALAXY_JOB_TMP_DIR`. Instead, a Galaxy server should set `TMPDIR`, `TMP` and others to `GALAXY_JOB_TMP_DIR` or any other folder that works for you.\n\nFor example, there are tools that don't like an NFS shared temporary location. In that case a user probably want to change `TMPDIR` for this specific tool to something else. If the tool would hardcode `GALAXY_JOB_TMP_DIR` this will not work.\n\nI hope that makes sense, please let me know if you have any other questions or if you need help to set your environment variables.","files":null}]}